title: Crockpot Black Bean Tortilla Soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas in crockpot, cook on low 8 hours.

Preheat oven to 400Â°F Lightly spray both sides of tortillas with nonstick cooking spray. Cut into thin strips (about5" x 0.5") and spread onto baking sheet. Bake, turning occasionally until crisp, 5-10 minutes.
Sprinkle tortilla strips over hot soup and serve immediately.
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can black beans, drained and rinsed
1 (15 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chilies
4 cups vegetable broth or 4 cups mock chicken broth
